   "body" : "The implementation of each class' serialization/deserialization is no longer passed within a macro.\r\nThe implementation now lies within a template of form:\r\n```\r\ntemplate <typename Stream, typename Operation>\r\ninline size_t SerializationOp(Stream& s, Operation ser_action, int nType, int nVersion) {\r\n    /* CODE */\r\n}\r\n```\r\nIn cases when codepath should depend on whether or not we are just deserializing\r\n(old **fGetSize**, **fWrite**, **fRead** flags) an additional clause can be used:\r\n```\r\nbool fRead = ser_action.ForRead();\r\n```\r\nThe **IMPLEMENT_SERIALIZE** macro will now be a freestanding clause added within class' body\r\n(similiar to Qt's **Q_OBJECT**) to implement **GetSerializeSize**, **Serialize** and **Unserialize**.\r\nThese are now wrappers around the **SerializationOp** template.",
